content.description:
Follow broken finger cracks straight up to the shiny anchor shared with

Mattrimoney

.
content.protection: A standard rack with an emphasis on small cams and wires.
content.location:
Follow broken finger cracks left of

That’s My Bush

. This shares the final 5 feet with

Mattrimoney

after

Mattrimoney

traverses far right. It also shares an anchor with

Mattrminoney

. Basically follow the line where the rope is hanging in the photo, though down low the first finger crack is a bit left of where the rope is hanging in the photo.

content.description: Work your way up a slab to a crack system and under a large block.  An undercling reveals the crux with easy climbing at the top.
content.protection: A standard rack down to a 0.2. Anchor off a ponderosa up top with hefty extension to reduce rope drag.
content.location:
Make your way left/uphill of

Bullwhip

to the next panel; this route is to the left of

That’s My Bush

and follows a clear crack before it traverses under a large block.

content.description: Work your way up through slab, crack, flake of varying integrity, and more crack to the top. Build a gear anchor, sling a rock, or use the ponderosa if you must for an anchor.
content.protection: A standard rack, and build your own anchor.
content.location:
This route is the first route uphill of

Bullwhip

.

content.description:
This route starts to the right of

Underklingon

. Work your way up, taking care not to yard on the ponderosa wall sapling; the mantel above the sapling is the crux with good climbing above it. The top may be a tad run out when you exit the final crack on your way to your anchor point at the upper ponderosa.
content.protection:
#0.2-#1 Camalots with some nuts should suffice. Build your own anchor.

Per

Cara Dee

: there is now a bolted anchor.
content.location:
It is 100 feet left/uphill of

Bull Whip

and 15 feet to the right of

Upperklingon

.
